Top positive reviewSee all 70 positive reviews› 
          5 people found this helpful
5.0 out of 5 starsFantastic political thriller that EVERYONE will enjoy!ByA. Hineson August 15, 2016This political thriller from David Pepper, frankly, far exceeded my expectations. I was rather skeptical of this first novel from someone who's well known in Ohio politics but who has never written a book and I have to say I was stunned when I realized this guy can write! I am a lawyer and a thriller aficionado so my standards were very high. I truly enjoyed The People's House!This book took me for a ride from the moment I opened until the very last page and the detail was amazing. It won't matter which way your politics lean and it will not matter if you live in Nevada or Texas, you get sucked into this story that takes you from rural communities in Ohio to the Siberian tundra in Russia. I'm not a fan of giving away the plot of the books I read but if you like John Grisham or David Baldacci... You, too, will be hoping that Pepper's next book isn't far behind!

Read more
