PEPPER - salt water swimming pool maintenance | APi - Pool and Water Care Chemical Products











































 Help Contact Us Where To Buy




































The Perfect Ingredient for Salt Water Pools



The Perfect Ingredient for Salt Water Pools





Product InfoUsage & Guidelines










PEPPER® is the perfect ingredient for salt water pools. It is a special blend of select ingredients formulated to work specifically with the unique demands of salt water pools. Adding PEPPER to your pool will enhance water quality, protect equipment, and reduce overall maintenance.
Use PEPPER regularly to:


Increase the life and performance of the salt water generator
Improve sanitizer effectiveness
Greatly enhance water clarity
Limit troublesome pH fluctuations
Prevent scale buildup on the generator cell, pool equipment and surfaces
Help maintain low phosphate levels

PEPPER is compatible with all pool surfaces and equipment, plus there is no waiting to swim. After the initial application, most salt water generators can be operated at lower settings. Use just twice a month to keep your salt water swimming pool perfectly seasoned!





What PEPPER does for your pool:

Greatly enhances water clarity – oxidizes debris and enhances filter performance
Provides extended protection for pool equipment and the generator cell
Significantly reduces pool maintenance – fewer chemical balance adjustments and less cleaning

















What PEPPER does for your pool:

Greatly enhances water clarity – oxidizes debris and enhances filter performance
Provides extended protection for pool equipment and the generator cell
Significantly reduces pool maintenance – fewer chemical balance adjustments and less cleaning

















Step One
Balance...





Balance the pool water as follows:
pH: 7.2 – 7.4
Total Alkalinity: 80 – 120 ppm
Calcium Hardness: 250 – 400 ppm
CYA: 40 – 80 ppm
Salt Level: Refer to generator instructions






Step Two
Add PEPPER®...





Add PEPPER directly in front of jet or broadcast over pool surface with pump running.
Initial dosage: Add 1 lb. per 10,000 gallons
Every 2 weeks: Add 1/2 lb per 10,000 gallons






Step Three
Test chlorine...





Test chlorine level after 7 days and adjust generator as needed. You will find that most generators can be operated at lower settings.







































